# EverArt MCP Server Settings
# Use this file to configure the EverArt MCP server for Claude Desktop
#
# Format:
# SETTING_NAME=value
#
# Required Settings:
# -----------------
# EVERART_API_KEY - Your EverArt API key
#   This key is required for the EverArt MCP server to function
#
# Optional Settings:
# -----------------
# CONTAINER_NAME - Name of the Docker container (default: everart-mcp-server)
# DOCKER_IMAGE - Docker image name and tag (default: mcp/everart:latest)
# RESTART_CLAUDE - Whether to restart Claude Desktop if it's running (true/false, default: true)
#
# Examples:
# EVERART_API_KEY=your_api_key_here
# CONTAINER_NAME=my-everart-server
# DOCKER_IMAGE=mcp/everart:custom
# RESTART_CLAUDE=false
#
# Default settings (uncomment and modify as needed):
EVERART_API_KEY=
# CONTAINER_NAME=everart-mcp-server
# DOCKER_IMAGE=mcp/everart:latest
# RESTART_CLAUDE=true
